<item>
            <title>[FELIX-5994] endpoint property for host 0.0.0.0 not resolved</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-5994</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The JettyService allows configuring the host to &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt; or &lt;tt&gt;0.0.0.0&lt;/tt&gt; which both result binding to all interfaces. While this works fine, the endpoint property is only correctly set when the host is &lt;tt&gt;null&lt;/tt&gt;, but not when it is set to &lt;tt&gt;0.0.0.0&lt;/tt&gt;. In the latter case it remains &lt;tt&gt;0.0.0.0&lt;/tt&gt; (which potentially confuses down stream application depending on this endpoint property).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The problematic line of code seems to be in addEndpointProperties &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/felix/blob/trunk/http/jetty/src/main/java/org/apache/felix/http/jetty/internal/JettyService.java#L794&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
